-- American Greetings profit doubles
-- 
-- Thu Jun 21, 2007 9:08am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/21/us-americangreetings-results-idUSBNG18030520070621

 

 (Reuters) - American Greetings Corp. AM.N said its quarterly profit almost doubled exceeding Wall Street expectations, helped by higher sales of greeting cards in North America. 

 Net income for the first quarter rose to 30.1 million, or 54 cents a share, compared with $15.4 million, or 24 cents a share, reported a year ago. Analysts on average were expecting 34 cents per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Net sales rose over 3 percent to $418 million, beating analysts' average estimate of $393.9 million. American Greetings, the second-largest U.S. greeting card company behind Hallmark Cards Inc., reaffirmed its full-year earnings forecast of $1.35 to $1.55 per share, from continuing operations. Analysts on average were expecting the retailer to earn $1.35 per share, excluding items, for the period. American Greetings added that its board is expected to maintain the company's dividend policy. (Reporting by Swagata Gupta in Bangalore)